Parliament, Monday, 12 October 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development will tomorrow continue with the deliberations and clause-by-clause reading and amendments to the Upgrading of the Land Tenure Rights Amendment Bill, taking into consideration comments made by the public.
	
	Details of the virtual meeting are as follows:
	Date : Tuesday, 13 October 2020
	Time: 09:00 – 12:00
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meeting to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi at mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE, LAND REFORM AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT, NKOSI ZWELIVELILE MANDELA.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
	Name: Sureshinee Govender
	Parliamentary Communication Services
